MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: ECS iPad Deal; Hwang, SapuraCrest Dividends

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-03-28T21:30:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/malaysia-daybook-ecs-ipad-deal-hwang-sapuracrest-dividends.html
ECS ICT Bhd. (ESC MK) was awarded
distribution rights for Apple Inc.’s iPad in the Southeast Asian
nation, the company said in an exchange filing. It already
distributes other Apple products such as the MacBook notebooks
and iPod.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Hwang-DBS ( Malaysia ) Bhd. (HDBS MK), the stock brokerage,
doubled its interim dividend to 5 sen/share after announcing a
38% rise in 2Q net income to 23.2 million ringgit.
* SapuraCrest Petroleum Bhd. (SCRES MK) proposed a higher final
dividend of 5.5 sen/share after announcing 4Q net rose to 72.7
million ringgit.
* Jaya Tiasa Holdings Bhd. (JT MK), the Malaysian timber
producer and oil palm planter, said 3Q net income almost tripled
to 39.9 million ringgit on higher selling prices.
* Asia Bioenergy Technologies Bhd. (ABIO MK) got a six-month
extension to complete its share placement.
* London Biscuits Bhd. (LBB MK) requested a one-month extension
for its proposed share split.  MARKETS:
* Malaysia’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index fell 0.1 percent.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index dropped 0.5 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  lost 0.2 percent.
* Palm oil June-delivery futures advanced 0.6 percent to 3,282
ringgit a metric ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
